00:19.561 --> 00:21.980
♪ ME, ME, ME ♪

00:22.063 --> 00:23.982
♪ STICK 'EM UP ALL AROUND,
HERE COMES MIGHTY B ♪

00:24.065 --> 00:25.400
♪ BEE, BEE, BEE ♪

00:25.483 --> 00:29.195
♪ ♪

00:29.279 --> 00:30.613
♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:30.697 --> 00:33.450
♪ MIGHTY, MIGHTY B ♪

00:48.339 --> 00:50.800
- LOOK, CHESTER TURTLETON.

00:50.884 --> 00:53.803
NANA FINISHED
MY AUTHENTIC DANISH VEST.

00:53.887 --> 00:56.681
I GUESS THIS MEANS
I'M REALLY GOING TO SOLVANG,

00:56.765 --> 00:59.309
HOME OF ALL THINGS DANISH.

00:59.392 --> 01:02.061
- [sighs]

01:02.145 --> 01:03.313
- I KNOW YOU WISH
YOU COULD COME TOO, CHESTER,

01:03.396 --> 01:06.983
BUT YOU'RE GOING TO HAVE
SUCH A NICE TIME AT BESSIE'S,

01:07.066 --> 01:08.568
YOU WON'T EVEN REMEMBER
TO EMAIL ME.

01:08.651 --> 01:10.820
[laughs nervously]

01:10.904 --> 01:12.197
I'M JUST KIDDING.

01:12.280 --> 01:13.406
I'M SO BAD.

01:15.283 --> 01:17.285
[lively music]

01:17.368 --> 01:18.495
♪ ♪

01:18.578 --> 01:20.538
[telephone rings]

01:20.622 --> 01:22.165
- HOTEL HIGGENBOTTOM.

01:22.248 --> 01:24.959
HEY, HAPPY,
THAT'S NOT A HOSPITAL CORNER.

01:25.043 --> 01:27.754
- [grumbles]

01:27.837 --> 01:28.755
- HEY, BESSIE.

01:28.838 --> 01:30.465
- OH, HI, MILLIE.

01:30.548 --> 01:32.675
MY STAFF IS JUST ABOUT READY
FOR MR. TURTLETON'S ARRIVAL.

01:32.759 --> 01:36.095
CHECK-IN TIME: NOW!

01:37.263 --> 01:40.099
- CHESTER CAN'T SLEEP
WITHOUT HIS STUFFED TURTLE,

01:40.183 --> 01:43.436
AND HERE ARE SOME BUGS
FOR A TREAT IF HE'S GOOD.

01:43.520 --> 01:44.938
- OH, THE MINI BAR
AT HOTEL HIGGENBOTTOM

01:45.021 --> 01:46.356
IS FULLY STOCKED.

01:46.439 --> 01:46.940
WE GOT CRICKET COOKIES.

01:47.023 --> 01:47.607
WE GOT ROACH JERKY.

01:47.690 --> 01:49.651
WE GOT BEETLE BURRITOS.

01:49.734 --> 01:51.903
WE GOT MEALWORM PIE.

01:51.986 --> 01:53.905
RIGHT, HAPS?

01:53.988 --> 01:55.615
- 'KAY.

01:55.698 --> 01:56.658
WELL, I PACKED
PLENTY OF QUARTERS,

01:56.741 --> 02:00.703
SO I'LL CALL
AND CHECK ON CHESTER EVERY DAY.

02:00.787 --> 02:02.330
- NOT TO WORRY, MILL.

02:02.413 --> 02:04.040
I GOT SO MUCH
AWESOME STUFF PLANNED,

02:04.123 --> 02:05.166
HE WON'T HAVE TIME
TO BE HOMESICK.

02:05.250 --> 02:08.002
WE'RE GONNA MAKE SUSHI,
GO PARASAILING,

02:08.086 --> 02:10.588
TOUR AN ACTIVE VOLCANO,
LEARN HOW TO WALK A TIGHTROPE,

02:10.672 --> 02:12.715
DRIVE STICK SHIFT,
BRUNCH IN SAUSALITO,

02:12.799 --> 02:15.051
AND THEN I THOUGHT MAYBE

02:15.134 --> 02:16.219
WE COULD SWIM
WITH SOME BABY SHARKS.

02:16.302 --> 02:18.054
OH, BABY SHARKS ARE SO CUTE.
I LOVE BABY SHARKS.

02:18.137 --> 02:20.431
THEY'RE SO CUTE.
THEY'RE SO LITTLE.

02:20.515 --> 02:23.101
THEY'RE LITTLE SHARKS,
BUT THEY'RE SO CUTE STILL...

02:23.184 --> 02:26.729
I WAS JUST KIDDING
ABOUT THE SHARKS, CHESTER.

02:26.813 --> 02:27.939
ONLY NOT REALLY.

02:28.022 --> 02:30.066
COME ON!
LET'S DO THIS!

02:34.946 --> 02:36.072
[coughs]

02:36.155 --> 02:37.740
WE CHEATED DEATH!

02:37.824 --> 02:40.660
WE CHEATED DEATH!
- [sputtering]

02:44.289 --> 02:45.999
- OH, THESE GET ME EVERY TIME.

02:46.082 --> 02:48.293
THE SIZE RATIO IS SO OFF.

02:52.130 --> 02:53.089
WHAT'S UP, HOLLYWOOD?

02:53.173 --> 02:55.258
GIMME SOME GREEN.

02:55.717 --> 02:58.803
[disco music]

02:58.887 --> 03:00.013
DISCO SHELL!

03:00.096 --> 03:02.473
AWESOME!

03:02.557 --> 03:03.641
♪ ♪

03:03.725 --> 03:07.854
[line ringing]

03:15.904 --> 03:17.822
- [sadly]
OH!

03:18.698 --> 03:22.452
[upbeat music]

03:22.535 --> 03:28.374
♪ ♪

03:30.209 --> 03:35.423
[accordion music playing
and line ringing]

03:38.092 --> 03:40.637
- OKAY,
I GOT CORNED BEEF HASH,

03:40.720 --> 03:41.971
ONION SOUP,
TWO EGGS SUNNY SIDE UP.

03:42.055 --> 03:45.183
- WHAT ABOUT MY TUNA MELT?

03:45.266 --> 03:46.726
-<i> VOILA!</i>

03:46.809 --> 03:47.727
chime!

03:53.733 --> 03:56.069
WHOA!

03:56.152 --> 03:58.655
WHO NEEDS SNOW?
AM I RIGHT, CHESTER?

04:08.331 --> 04:12.210
- [someone screaming on TV]

04:12.293 --> 04:15.421
[upbeat accordion music]

04:18.423 --> 04:21.594
[door creaks]

04:21.678 --> 04:23.471
-<i> GODDAG!</i>

04:23.554 --> 04:27.225
THAT MEANS "HELLO" IN DANISH!

04:27.308 --> 04:29.560
[monster snarling]

04:29.644 --> 04:30.770
[people screaming on TV]

04:30.853 --> 04:32.480
<i>GODDAG!</i>

04:32.563 --> 04:33.564
[all scream]

04:35.566 --> 04:37.527
- TA-DA!

04:37.610 --> 04:41.197
- MILLIE, YOU'RE BACK EARLY.

04:41.281 --> 04:43.074
- CHESTER TURTLETON?

04:43.157 --> 04:47.996
- CHESTER, LOOK WHO'S HERE.

04:48.079 --> 04:49.288
- OH.

04:49.372 --> 04:51.082
- HE'S PROBABLY JUST SCARED
FROM THE MOVIE.

04:51.165 --> 04:54.002
A VAMPIRE WAS MARRYING
A WEREWOLF, SO...

04:54.085 --> 04:55.712
- COME ON, CHESTER.

04:55.795 --> 04:59.882
NANA'S MAKING CUPS OF HOT WATER
TO CELEBRATE YOUR RETURN.

05:01.968 --> 05:05.096
- OH, A GOOD-BYE SHAKE.

05:05.179 --> 05:06.973
I HAD FUN WITH YOU TOO, CHESTER.

05:07.056 --> 05:09.809
HE LOVES THE TASTE OF MY HAIR.

05:09.892 --> 05:11.019
OH!

05:14.856 --> 05:17.734
- I REALLY MISSED YOU,
CHESTER TURTLETON.

05:17.817 --> 05:20.028
SWEET DREAMS.

05:21.821 --> 05:26.993
[snoring loudly]

05:31.497 --> 05:35.585
- I MEAN, I WASN'T ABOUT TO
ARGUE OVER A SHOPPING CART.

05:35.668 --> 05:37.462
HAPPY, ARE YOU EVEN LISTENING?

05:41.382 --> 05:44.260
OH, IT'S GREAT TO SEE YOU,
GREEN STUFF.

05:44.343 --> 05:48.014
BUT YOU KNOW
YOU CAN'T STAY HERE.

05:48.097 --> 05:50.600
[knocking at door]

05:50.683 --> 05:53.102
OH, HE MUST HAVE FALLEN
INTO YOUR TOILET, SO...

05:53.186 --> 05:55.980
YOU'RE HOME, CHESTER.

05:56.064 --> 05:57.690
[doorbell rings]

05:59.776 --> 06:00.151
[knocking at door]

06:00.234 --> 06:01.402
[doorbell rings]

06:03.946 --> 06:06.032
[knocking at door]

06:06.115 --> 06:07.658
[doorbell rings]

06:10.912 --> 06:14.791
[knocking at door]

06:17.168 --> 06:19.378
- AS YOU KNOW,
CHESTER TURTLETON,

06:19.462 --> 06:21.964
I PREFER TO EXPRESS MY EMOTIONS
THROUGH SONG,

06:22.048 --> 06:24.342
SO I HAVE PREPARED A PIECE.

06:24.425 --> 06:26.302
A ONE, A TWO.
A ONE, TWO, THREE.

06:26.385 --> 06:28.971
[tunelessly]
♪ OH, CHESTER TURTLETON ♪

06:29.055 --> 06:31.682
♪ DO YOU REMEMBER ♪

06:31.766 --> 06:34.811
♪ WHEN I FILLED YOUR BOWL
WITH WATER ♪

06:34.894 --> 06:36.687
♪ AND BROUGHT YOU WORMS TO EAT ♪

06:36.771 --> 06:43.820
♪ BECAUSE YOU WERE HUNGRY
AND THAT'S WHAT TURTLES... ♪

06:43.903 --> 06:46.906
♪ EAT? ♪

06:46.989 --> 06:51.994
♪ ALSO, I MADE A BED FOR YOU
ON MY PILLOW ♪

06:52.078 --> 06:55.790
♪ AND DIDN'T COMPLAIN
WHEN YOU WET IT ♪

06:58.918 --> 07:02.505
[doorbell rings]

07:02.588 --> 07:05.216
CHESTER WON'T COME OUT
OF HIS SHELL.

07:05.299 --> 07:08.010
- OH, MILLIE,
HE'S PROBABLY JUST TIRED

07:08.094 --> 07:10.763
FROM ALL THE EXCITEMENT
OF BEING HOME.

07:10.847 --> 07:11.347
- I DON'T THINK SO.

07:11.430 --> 07:13.891
THE THRILL IS GONE.

07:13.975 --> 07:17.603
HE'S LOST HIS "JOY DE VIVRAY."

07:17.687 --> 07:19.897
- WELL, MAYBE YOU NEED
TO SPICE THINGS UP.

07:19.981 --> 07:22.191
- I DID THAT.

07:22.275 --> 07:23.943
I EVEN TRIED PLAYING
OPPOSITE-SIDE CHECKERS,

07:24.026 --> 07:26.028
BUT IT MADE ME TOO ANXIOUS.

07:26.112 --> 07:27.864
- OPPOSITE-SIDE CHECKERS?

07:27.947 --> 07:30.199
- UH-HUH.
USUALLY, WE'RE BOTH BLACK.

07:30.283 --> 07:32.243
- YOU MEAN CHECKERS.

07:32.326 --> 07:34.412
- OPPOSITE-SIDE CHECKERS.

07:34.495 --> 07:36.455
- RIGHT, SO PLAIN CHECKERS.

07:36.539 --> 07:37.039
YOU PLAYED CHECKERS.

07:37.123 --> 07:39.417
- I'M AT MY WIT'S END.

07:39.500 --> 07:41.419
MAYBE YOU SHOULD JUST TAKE HIM.

07:41.502 --> 07:41.919
- BUT, MILLIE,
HE'S PROBABLY JUST--

07:42.003 --> 07:44.005
- PLEASE, BESSIE.

07:44.088 --> 07:46.090
HE'S HAPPIER HERE.

07:46.174 --> 07:50.511
[melancholy cello music]

07:53.973 --> 07:57.560
- LOOK, EVERYBODY.
CHESTER'S BACK.

07:57.643 --> 07:58.769
YAY!

07:58.853 --> 08:00.313
- [indignant barking]

08:00.396 --> 08:02.481
-<i> YOU</i> PUT THE TURTLE DOWN.

08:02.565 --> 08:03.733
<i>YOU</i> GET BACK TO WORK.

08:03.816 --> 08:05.484
I DO NOT ALWAYS SKIP OUT
ON LUNCH.

08:08.070 --> 08:10.072
HUH! TRY TO TELL ME
I'M NOT PULLING MY WEIGHT.

08:10.156 --> 08:11.866
I'LL TELL YOU
TO PULL YOUR OWN WEIGHT.

08:11.949 --> 08:13.659
SORRY YOU HAD TO SEE THAT, CHES,

08:13.743 --> 08:14.577
BUT YOU ARE
ONE OF THE FAMILY NOW.

08:14.660 --> 08:17.955
NO MORE FANCY MANNERS
AND GUEST TOWELS.

08:18.039 --> 08:20.458
WATCH THIS, HAPS!

08:27.715 --> 08:31.469
[grumbling]
PULL MY WEIGHT. PULL THIS!

08:33.054 --> 08:36.682
- THIS ISN'T
THE CALIFORNIA PLATE!

08:36.765 --> 08:38.351
- CHESTER!

08:39.936 --> 08:41.979
- [sighs in relief]

08:42.063 --> 08:43.105
[footsteps approaching]

08:43.188 --> 08:45.441
- MY HAM SANDWICH, HAPPY!
GIVE IT!

08:45.524 --> 08:47.235
boing!

08:53.991 --> 08:56.035
- [coughs]

08:57.870 --> 08:59.664
- GOOD NIGHT, CHESTER!

08:59.747 --> 09:00.748
OH, BUT WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

09:00.831 --> 09:03.042
FIRST I GOT A GOOD ONE FOR YA.

09:03.125 --> 09:04.877
COME ON. COME ON.
COME ON. COME ON.

09:04.961 --> 09:08.381
IF YOU GO INSIDE YOUR SHELL,
I'LL TELL YOU A JOKE!

09:08.464 --> 09:10.299
KNOCK, KNOCK.

09:10.383 --> 09:11.300
WHAT'S BLACK AND WHITE
AND WALKS LIKE A PENGUIN?

09:11.384 --> 09:12.551
A PENGUIN.
HA HA HA HA!

09:12.635 --> 09:15.721
OKAY, NO, WAIT;
THAT WAS MORE OF A RIDDLE.

09:15.805 --> 09:17.306
OKAY, THIS ONE'S A CLASSIC.

09:17.390 --> 09:19.392
ONCE THERE WAS A LEPRECHAUN
WHO WALKED--AH! NO.

09:19.475 --> 09:22.103
IT'S ST. PATRICK'S DAY, RIGHT?

09:22.186 --> 09:23.646
AND THERE'S A PERSON
THAT WALKS INTO A BAR.

09:23.729 --> 09:25.898
A BARTENDER IS SERVING A MAN
WHO LOOKS LIKE A LEPRECHAUN,

09:25.982 --> 09:27.900
BUT HE ISN'T, AND HE SAYS
"WHAT ARE YOU DRINKING?"

09:27.984 --> 09:29.652
AND THE BARTENDER SAYS,
"I'M A LEPRECHAUN."

09:29.735 --> 09:32.446
NO.
OKAY, CLEAR YOUR MIND.

09:34.657 --> 09:37.159
CHESTER!
JOIN THE FUN!

09:37.243 --> 09:39.537
WE'RE POOPED, SO WE'RE HAVING
A DANCE PARTY PILLOW FIGHT

09:39.620 --> 09:40.705
TILL WE PASS OUT!

09:43.249 --> 09:46.961
[laughing]

09:53.426 --> 09:55.511
ARR! ARR!

09:55.594 --> 09:58.347
WHA--IS THAT ANY WAY
TO TALK TO A PIRATE?

09:58.431 --> 10:02.810
[snoring]

10:05.563 --> 10:10.568
- ♪ OH, CHESTER TURTLETON,
DO YOU REMEMBER ♪

10:10.651 --> 10:13.529
♪ WHEN I FILLED YOUR BOWL
WITH WATER ♪

10:13.612 --> 10:15.781
♪ AND BROUGHT YOU WORMS TO EAT ♪

10:15.865 --> 10:20.369
♪ BECAUSE YOU WERE HUNGRY
AND THAT'S WHAT TURTLES EAT? ♪

10:20.453 --> 10:23.164
♪ OH, CHESTER TURTLETON ♪

10:23.247 --> 10:25.291
♪ YOU'RE THE TURTLE FOR ME ♪

10:25.374 --> 10:27.251
♪ YOU ARE THE BESTEST AMPHIBIAN
I EVER MET ♪

10:27.335 --> 10:29.670
♪ INCLUDING FROGS ♪

10:29.754 --> 10:34.383
♪ AND YOU FILL MY HEART
WITH GLEE ♪

10:34.467 --> 10:42.350
♪ ♪

11:01.410 --> 11:03.204
AH, SO LONG, GREEN STUFF.

11:03.287 --> 11:06.165
NO HARD FEELINGS.

11:06.248 --> 11:09.543
LIFE MOVES PRETTY FAST
AT HOTEL HIGGENBOTTOM.

11:16.342 --> 11:18.135
- CHESTER!

11:18.219 --> 11:21.138
I SET YOU FREE,
AND YOU CAME BACK,

11:21.222 --> 11:24.600
AND SO NOW YOU'RE MINE FOREVER.

11:24.683 --> 11:26.310
NEE NEE NEE NEE NEE.

11:26.394 --> 11:29.271
NEE NEE NEE NEE
NEE NEE.

11:29.355 --> 11:31.732
LITTLE LITTLE CHESTER SHELL BOY.

11:45.871 --> 11:46.997
- IS THAT ALL YOU GOT?

11:47.081 --> 11:48.707
YOU CALL THAT PARRYING?

11:48.791 --> 11:50.751
TAKE OFF THE TRAINING WHEELS
ALREADY.

11:50.835 --> 11:52.461
- [barks vehemently]

11:52.545 --> 11:56.090
- A FIRST MATE DOES NOT SPEAK
THAT WAY TO HIS CAPTAIN.

11:56.173 --> 11:57.716
- [barks]

11:57.800 --> 11:58.968
- HA!

11:59.051 --> 12:02.721
NO, I WEAR THE FANCY HAT,
SO I AM THE CAPTAIN.

12:02.805 --> 12:05.474
CHECK THE PIRATES' CODE.

12:05.558 --> 12:07.435
- HUH?
[growling]

12:07.518 --> 12:10.479
- AH, AGAIN
WITH THE INSUBORDINATION.

12:10.563 --> 12:14.108
RESPECT THE HAAAAT!

12:23.534 --> 12:25.161
- [laughs]

12:25.244 --> 12:27.705
- VERY FUNNY, DR. FRANKENSTEIN.

12:27.788 --> 12:28.914
UGH!

12:28.998 --> 12:31.250
LOOK WHAT WE DID.

12:31.333 --> 12:33.919
[gasps]

12:34.003 --> 12:36.672
WHAT IS THAT?

12:36.755 --> 12:38.299
AMATEUR PAWS ASIDE.

12:38.382 --> 12:41.260
THIS REQUIRES A CERTIFIED
ARCHEOLOGY BADGE HOLDER.

12:44.805 --> 12:46.348
WHOA!

12:46.432 --> 12:47.641
A SOLID GOLD NUGGET.

12:47.725 --> 12:50.227
HAPPY, DO YOU KNOW
WHAT THIS MEANS?

12:50.311 --> 12:51.854
I'LL SPELL IT OUT FOR YOU:

12:51.937 --> 12:53.022
DOLLAR SIGN, DOLLAR SIGN,

12:53.105 --> 12:54.482
DOLLAR SIGN, DOLLAR SIGN,
DOLLAR SIGN.

12:54.565 --> 12:55.941
WE'RE RICH!

12:56.025 --> 12:56.525
[giggling]

12:56.609 --> 12:59.361
NOW, HOLD ON A SEC.

12:59.445 --> 13:01.363
TRADITIONALLY, THE CAPTAIN--
THAT WOULD BE MOI--

13:01.447 --> 13:04.492
RECEIVES TWO SHARES OF A BOUNTY,
WHILE THE FIRST MATE--

13:04.575 --> 13:07.453
THAT WOULD BE TOI--
GETS ONE AND A HALF SHARES.

13:07.536 --> 13:08.537
AND WHO ARE WE
TO BUCK TRADITION?

13:08.621 --> 13:09.914
- [barks angrily]

13:09.997 --> 13:11.499
- WELL, IF I HADN'T BROKEN
THE WALL,

13:11.582 --> 13:13.042
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE SPOTTED IT.

13:13.125 --> 13:15.044
- [barks angrily]

13:15.127 --> 13:15.961
- OKAY, OKAY,
WE'LL SPLIT IT EQUALLY.

13:18.047 --> 13:19.882
THIS THING IS BEAUTIFUL.

13:19.965 --> 13:23.219
IT MUST BE WORTH A MILLION--
NO, A TRILLION--

13:23.302 --> 13:28.182
NO, BAJILLION--
NO, A KAJILLION DOLLAR SIGNS.

13:28.265 --> 13:31.727
AND NOW TO MY 17th FAVORITE
PLACE TO CONDUCT BUSINESS.

13:32.978 --> 13:34.813
[bicycle bell rings]

13:37.316 --> 13:39.902
DEPOSIT SLIP.

13:39.985 --> 13:41.737
GOLD NUGGET.

13:45.157 --> 13:48.827
AND A POSTCARD SO IT CAN WRITE
TO US FROM THE VAULT.

13:48.911 --> 13:50.496
HA HA, JUST KIDDING, HAPS.

13:50.579 --> 13:53.165
GOLD CAN'T WRITE.
IT'S JUST A MINERAL.

13:56.377 --> 13:58.254
NOW IS THE PERFECT TIME

13:58.337 --> 14:00.422
TO OPEN A JUNIOR SAVINGS ACCOUNT
FOR YOU.

14:00.506 --> 14:01.298
FIRST WE'LL DEPOSIT YOUR GOLD,
AND THEN...

14:01.382 --> 14:02.800
- [barks angrily]

14:02.883 --> 14:05.678
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"BANKS CAN'T BE TRUSTED"?

14:05.761 --> 14:07.930
DOES YOUR MATTRESS PAY YOU
INTEREST?

14:08.013 --> 14:10.349
IS YOUR SOCK DRAWER
FEDERALLY INSURED?

14:10.432 --> 14:12.768
THE ANSWER IS EITHER "NO"
OR "NOT AT COMPETITIVE RATES."

14:12.851 --> 14:17.398
SHE WHO WEARS THE CAPTAIN'S HAT
KNOWS BEST.

14:17.481 --> 14:19.567
- [barking]

14:19.650 --> 14:23.112
- FINE, HAPPY, BUT TRY TO
EXERCISE A LITTLE RESTRAINT.

14:23.195 --> 14:26.365
EVERYONE KNOWS ALL YOU DO
IS SPEND, SPEND, SPEND.

14:26.448 --> 14:29.994
AND NOW...

14:30.077 --> 14:32.913
LET'S GO BE RICH!

14:32.997 --> 14:36.125
- HUH, TEN DOLLAR SIGNS.

14:36.208 --> 14:39.837
[upbeat music]

14:39.920 --> 14:42.840
- OOH, I'VE ALWAYS WANTED
A MAKE-YOUR-OWN-PIÑATA KIT.

14:42.923 --> 14:44.550
AND MINIATURE STAPLERS.

14:44.633 --> 14:47.386
A SANTA CLAUS
THAT SINGS <i> AND</i> DANCES?

14:47.469 --> 14:49.138
WHO THINKS UP THIS STUFF?

14:49.221 --> 14:51.890
CHARGE IT AND BILL ME LATER.

14:53.726 --> 14:55.311
[rumbling]

14:56.895 --> 14:58.439
HEY, MAURICE,
NICE TO SEE YA AGAIN.

14:58.522 --> 14:59.440
BILL ME LATER.

14:59.523 --> 15:00.816
JERRY, WHATCHA GOT?

15:00.899 --> 15:04.486
YOU KNOW THE DRILL;
BILL ME LATER.

15:04.570 --> 15:06.155
[bell rings]

15:06.238 --> 15:07.364
[all murmuring in awe]

15:07.448 --> 15:10.451
I'M RICH.

15:10.534 --> 15:11.619
CHING!

15:11.702 --> 15:12.828
- WHOA!

15:12.911 --> 15:15.623
- SHE'S SO RICH.

15:15.706 --> 15:18.083
- DOUBLE SCOOPS FOR EVERYONE,
ON ME.

15:18.167 --> 15:20.044
CHOCOLATE SAUCE FLOWS FREE
TODAY.

15:20.127 --> 15:21.045
[all cheering]

15:21.128 --> 15:21.962
PUT IT ON MY TAB.

15:30.054 --> 15:31.847
- HUH?

15:31.930 --> 15:33.682
[disapproving grunt]

15:33.766 --> 15:35.434
- OH, HAPPY, YOU'RE STILL
NOT USED TO THE FACT

15:35.517 --> 15:38.812
THAT WE'RE RICH, RICH!

15:49.114 --> 15:50.616
buzz!

15:50.699 --> 15:53.202
- HI, MS. BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM,
RICH PERSON.

15:53.285 --> 15:55.454
I JUST NEED TO PAY
A COUPLE OF BILLS TODAY.

15:55.537 --> 15:57.081
THANKS.

16:01.919 --> 16:05.547
[computer beeping]

16:05.631 --> 16:07.716
- THIS STACK WILL BE PAID
IN FULL.

16:07.800 --> 16:10.219
THIS STACK CANNOT BE PAID
DUE TO INSUFFICIENT FUNDS.

16:10.302 --> 16:12.638
- HMM.

16:12.721 --> 16:13.639
WHY, THAT MUST BE SOME SORT
OF ERROR ON YOUR PART.

16:13.722 --> 16:15.974
CHECK AGAIN, MY GOOD MAN.

16:18.310 --> 16:21.063
- INSUFFICIENT FUNDS.

16:21.146 --> 16:24.692
- INSUFFICIENT FUNDS?
AS IN NO MONEY?

16:24.775 --> 16:26.735
UM, I'M NOT SURE
YOU UNDERSTAND.

16:26.819 --> 16:31.573
YOU SEE, I RECENTLY DEPOSITED
A GOLD NUGGET.

16:31.657 --> 16:34.576
IT'S WORTH BETWEEN A BAJILLION
AND A KAJILLION DOLLAR SIGNS.

16:34.660 --> 16:36.078
BASICALLY, I'M RICH.

16:36.161 --> 16:39.707
- SIR, I'M LOOKING
AT YOUR GOLD NUGGET TRANSACTION,

16:39.790 --> 16:40.749
AND IT WAS WORTH
TEN DOLLAR SIGNS.

16:40.833 --> 16:43.627
THESE BILLS ARE TWICE AS MUCH.

16:43.711 --> 16:44.670
- UH...

16:44.753 --> 16:46.046
PARDON?

16:46.130 --> 16:48.173
- IT'S TEN DOLLAR SIGNS.

16:51.510 --> 16:52.302
- HOW CAN I BE BROKE?

16:52.386 --> 16:55.264
SINCE WHEN DOES GELATO BREAK
THE BANK?

16:55.347 --> 16:58.600
I GUESS 500 DOUBLE SCOOPS
REALLY ADDS UP.

16:58.684 --> 17:00.185
THEY SHOULD WARN YOU.

17:00.269 --> 17:01.353
[telephone rings]

17:01.437 --> 17:02.980
HIGGENBOTTOM.

17:03.063 --> 17:05.107
- HELLO, THIS IS
THE KAYAK EMPORIUM CALLING

17:05.190 --> 17:08.318
ABOUT THE MANY DOLLAR SIGNS
YOU OWE US.

17:08.402 --> 17:09.403
- OH!

17:09.486 --> 17:10.612
[telephone rings]

17:10.695 --> 17:12.865
HIGGENBOTTOM BEEBERRY.

17:12.948 --> 17:14.491
- UH, YEAH,
THIS IS THE TOY STORE CALLING

17:14.575 --> 17:16.160
ABOUT YOUR UNPAID TAB.

17:16.242 --> 17:18.369
- AH!

17:18.454 --> 17:20.705
[knocking at door]

17:20.789 --> 17:27.963
- DOLLAR SIGNS DUE NOOOOOW.

17:28.047 --> 17:29.089
- [screams]

17:32.885 --> 17:33.635
- DOLLAR SIGNS!

17:33.719 --> 17:36.138
- DOLLAR SIGNS!

17:36.221 --> 17:39.224
- DOLLAR SIIIIGNS!

17:39.308 --> 17:40.934
- AHH!
OKAY, OKAY!

17:41.018 --> 17:43.145
A WHOLE BUNCH OF DOLLAR SIGNS
COMING RIGHT UP.

17:49.943 --> 17:51.987
- EVERY MONTH,
PUT 20% OF YOUR DOLLAR SIGNS

17:52.070 --> 17:54.823
IN A SEPARATE SAVINGS ACCOUNT
OR HIGH-INTEREST MATTRESS.

17:54.907 --> 17:56.658
- HAPS?

17:56.742 --> 17:58.660
UM, DUE TO A BANKING ERROR

17:58.744 --> 18:01.079
THAT SEVERELY DEVALUED
MY IMMENSE WEALTH,

18:01.163 --> 18:03.832
I AM NOW IN A SITUATION
WITH THESE ZOMBIE CREDITORS,

18:03.916 --> 18:04.792
WHO ARE AFTER ME
FOR MY UNPAID BILLS.

18:04.875 --> 18:07.669
- zombies: DOLLAR SIGNS!

18:07.753 --> 18:11.882
DOLLAR SIIIIIGNS!

18:11.965 --> 18:14.343
- SO I NEED TO BORROW--
OR POSSIBLY RECEIVE AS A GIFT,

18:14.426 --> 18:17.846
DEPENDING ON HOW MUCH YOU VALUE
ALL I'VE DONE FOR YOU--

18:17.930 --> 18:19.181
YOUR HALF OF THE GOLD
TO PAY THEM OFF

18:19.264 --> 18:22.017
BEFORE THEY EAT MY BRAINS
AND RUIN MY CREDIT RATING.

18:22.100 --> 18:23.310
[video rewinding]

18:23.393 --> 18:25.270
- NEVER MIX FRIENDS AND MONEY.

18:25.354 --> 18:26.522
- BUT, HAPS, MY CREDIT RATING.

18:26.605 --> 18:31.318
I NEED THAT GOLD.

18:31.401 --> 18:33.737
- KNOW THE DIFFERENCE
BETWEEN NEED AND WANT.

18:33.821 --> 18:36.865
WHO'S REALLY TO BLAME IF ALL
YOU DO IS SPEND, SPEND, SPEND?

18:37.783 --> 18:42.371
- DOLLAR SIGNS!

18:42.454 --> 18:44.414
- OKAY, OKAY, I ADMIT IT.

18:44.498 --> 18:45.457
I MAY HAVE BEEN
A TAD IRRESPONSIBLE

18:45.541 --> 18:47.876
AND CAUSED MY OWN MASSIVE
FINANCIAL DOWNFALL.

18:47.960 --> 18:48.919
OH, THAT HURT!

18:49.002 --> 18:51.672
- [barks]

18:51.755 --> 18:54.633
- YOU'RE THE CAPTAIN.
I'M THE FIRST MATE.

18:54.716 --> 18:55.884
GOT IT.

18:55.968 --> 18:57.177
- [barks]

18:57.261 --> 18:57.928
- MY CAPTAIN'S HAT?

18:58.011 --> 19:00.305
BUT YOU ALREADY HAVE THE TITLE.

19:00.639 --> 19:01.974
FINE.

19:02.057 --> 19:04.685
I NOW PRONOUNCE YOU
CAPTAIN AND HAT.

19:04.768 --> 19:06.436
HERE.

19:06.520 --> 19:07.145
- HA!

19:07.229 --> 19:09.189
- HAPPY, I GAVE YOU MY HAT.

19:09.273 --> 19:11.400
WHAT MORE DO YOU WANT?

19:11.483 --> 19:12.401
[cheerful music]

19:12.484 --> 19:13.944
BON APPETIT, CAPTAIN HAPPY.

19:14.027 --> 19:16.613
SO JUST PANCAKES,
AND I GET THE GOLD?

19:16.697 --> 19:19.992
- DOLLAR SIGNS!

19:20.075 --> 19:22.369
- WHAT'S THIS?

19:27.374 --> 19:29.084
YOU MADE A TREASURE MAP
OF WHERE YOU HID THE GOLD

19:29.167 --> 19:30.377
AND YOU'RE ONLY GONNA GIVE ME

19:30.460 --> 19:31.086
ONE TEENY, TINY, LITTLE PIECE
OF THE MAP

19:31.169 --> 19:33.088
FOR EVERY CHORE I DO FOR YOU?

19:33.172 --> 19:34.965
BUT--
- [barks vehemently]

19:35.048 --> 19:38.010
- SHOULD'VE KNOWN; IT'S NEVER
JUST PANCAKES WITH YOU.

19:38.093 --> 19:42.389
♪ ♪

19:42.472 --> 19:43.599
[squawks]

19:46.143 --> 19:48.353
DONE.

19:50.522 --> 19:53.150
- DOLLAR SIGNS!

20:00.866 --> 20:01.867
- THIS IS IT!

20:01.950 --> 20:03.702
"X" MARKS THE SPOT.

20:03.785 --> 20:06.622
- DOLLAR SIGNS!
- DOLLAR SIGNS!

20:06.705 --> 20:08.040
[suspenseful music]

20:08.123 --> 20:09.499
♪ ♪

20:09.583 --> 20:10.792
- OOH, GETTING WARMER.

20:10.876 --> 20:12.794
EUREKA!

20:12.878 --> 20:14.796
HUH?

20:14.880 --> 20:16.423
THERE'S NOTHING HERE.

20:19.718 --> 20:21.261
[sweeping orchestral music]

20:21.345 --> 20:23.639
HEY, WHAT'S THE BIG IDEA?

20:23.722 --> 20:25.891
I EARNED YOUR GOLD
FAIR AND SQUARE.

20:25.974 --> 20:28.810
- [barks happily]

20:28.894 --> 20:30.687
- PIRATES' CODE?

20:30.771 --> 20:33.690
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'D USE
THE PIRATES' CODE AGAINST ME.

20:33.774 --> 20:34.316
UGH!

20:34.399 --> 20:35.275
NOW, HAND OVER THAT GOLD,

20:35.359 --> 20:38.153
OR YOU'LL TASTE THE STING
OF MY STINGER.

20:38.236 --> 20:39.863
COME BACK HERE AND FIGHT
LIKE A PIRATE,

20:39.947 --> 20:41.657
YOU BLUE-BELLIED COWARD!

20:41.740 --> 20:43.909
YOU DON'T DESERVE THAT HAT.

20:43.992 --> 20:45.410
- DOLLAR SIGNS!
- DOLLAR SIGNS!

20:53.794 --> 20:56.964
- WHOA!

21:13.647 --> 21:15.649
HA!

21:24.616 --> 21:28.370
- [whimpering]

21:28.453 --> 21:30.205
- WHA-HA!

21:30.288 --> 21:32.290
- DOLLAR SIGNS!

21:32.374 --> 21:35.210
DUE NOW!

21:45.971 --> 21:47.097
- UH, WHOA.

21:47.180 --> 21:48.473
LET'S SEE HERE.

21:48.557 --> 21:49.683
OH.
A-HA!

21:49.766 --> 21:51.685
I THOUGHT THERE WAS
A MOBY DICK BADGE.

21:51.768 --> 21:52.394
HOW 'BOUT IT, HAPS?

21:52.477 --> 21:55.272
I'LL LET YOU CALL ME ISHMAEL.

21:58.317 --> 22:01.069
UH, WE'RE GOING TO NEED
AN EXTENSION.

22:01.153 --> 22:03.071
JUST ONE MORE DAY,
A FEW HOURS.

22:03.155 --> 22:06.199
AND WE'LL GET YOUR EYE BACK.

22:08.952 --> 22:11.788
OOH, OOPS.
YOUR ARM CAME OFF.

22:13.457 --> 22:14.833
OH, I'LL JUST--
HERE YA GO. OKAY.

22:14.916 --> 22:17.669
THAT LOOKS NICE.

22:21.089 --> 22:23.425
HAPS, ARRRR YOU GONNA STEER?

22:23.508 --> 22:24.676
HA HA, GET IT?

22:24.760 --> 22:26.386
DON'T WORRY;
I GOT ENOUGH PIRATE JOKES

22:26.470 --> 22:28.597
TO LAST THROUGH ALL SEVEN SEAS.

22:28.680 --> 22:30.432
ARRRR YA EXCITED?

22:30.515 --> 22:32.309
HA HA, THAT'S ANOTHER ONE
RIGHT THERE.

22:32.392 --> 22:33.894
- [sighs wearily]

